text: There's a period in the older Sam Sulek videos where his sleep schedule is so fucked he goes to the gym in the deepest hours of the night and the sun is actually rising by the time he's done with the workout and resting in his car afterwards, "morning crowd" coming in again, etc.
Imagine exiting the gym and dawn breaks, roosters crow, first rays of sun slip above the horizon. Must be so reinvigorating.

A door-to-door salesman knocked on my apartment door today, hadn't had one do in over a decade now. That's like a post-Soviet, Great Depression era type job, selling encyclopedias and kitchen utensils to ghetto households, don't see a lot of them nowadays. Wonder what it means...
Can you tell him to read Ray Peat's articles on rate of living and altitude if you talk 1 on  1  theoretically.......
